cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with decision problems for quantifier-free formulas with linear inequalities. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper mentions applications in program analysis. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a preprocessing phase to improve the efficiency of the decision procedure. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of simplex-based decision procedures. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also relevant as the paper discusses the use of SMT solvers in software verification and model-checking.
